            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2022-02-07 13:54:52" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>pertaining to being poor and destitute, implying a continuous state</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>poor</Gloss>
                <Gloss>destitute</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>See comments at {D:57.51}.|Since in all societies there are poor people, there is no difficulty involved in finding a suitable expression to designate such persons, but in some languages idiomatic phrases are used, for example, ‘those who walk in rags’ or ‘those whose ribs are always showing.’</Comments>
